WEBVTT

00:03.903 --> 00:07.202
<i>##[Chorus Singing]</i>

00:10.143 --> 00:12.168
<i>[Bell Ringing]</i>

00:12.278 --> 00:14.178
[Tires Screeching]

00:15.415 --> 00:17.508
D'oh!
[Screams]

00:19.000 --> 00:25.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:34.401 --> 00:36.562
Whoa-ho!
Texas snowball fight!

00:36.669 --> 00:38.637
[Both Laughing]

00:40.807 --> 00:43.401
Ow! Bart,
that has nuts in it.

00:45.412 --> 00:48.040
Hey, I thought your mother
told you to take a bath.

00:48.148 --> 00:50.013
Yeah, Mom says
a lot of things.

00:50.116 --> 00:53.279
Oh, I understand, kids.
I'm not a bath man myself.

00:53.386 --> 00:56.651
- More of a cologne man.
- Actually, we can't take a bath anyway.

00:56.756 --> 01:00.988
- The water heater is broken.
- Don't worry. Daddy will fix it.

01:01.094 --> 01:02.994
Hmm.

01:04.063 --> 01:05.964
[Grunting]

01:09.536 --> 01:11.470
Out of my way!
She's gonna blow.

01:17.710 --> 01:19.610
What on earth?

01:19.712 --> 01:22.613
Hi, sweetie.
I'm off to Moe's. Love ya.

01:22.715 --> 01:25.081
[Tires Squealing]

01:25.185 --> 01:28.279
<i>To Marge and all</i>
<i>the blissful years...</i>

01:28.388 --> 01:31.323
I've spent hiding
from her in this bar.

01:31.424 --> 01:33.324
[All]
Hear! Hear!

01:33.426 --> 01:36.884
Yeah, big deal. You got a wife.
I got a rash. Who cares?

01:38.398 --> 01:41.060
Uh, I'm sorry, Homer.

01:41.167 --> 01:44.603
It's just- It's been four years since
my last date with a whatchacallit...

01:44.704 --> 01:47.935
- uh, woman.
- Whatever happened to your mail-order bride?

01:48.041 --> 01:50.305
Oh, she got homesick
for her old life-

01:50.410 --> 01:53.470
diving for tourists' pennies
in a Micronesian swamp.

01:53.580 --> 01:56.708
- So, her career got in the way.
- Yeah. I don't blame her.

01:56.816 --> 02:00.274
No girl wants to end up
with a Joe Puke-Pail like me.

02:00.386 --> 02:03.651
Now, now, I won't hear of it, Moe.
You're a fabulous catch.

02:03.756 --> 02:05.883
Oh, yeah? Well, uh,
how come I ain't...

02:05.992 --> 02:08.517
fending off movie starlets
with a pointy stick?

02:08.627 --> 02:10.925
Oh, it's probably
due to your ugliness.

02:11.030 --> 02:13.590
But that doesn't mean
we can't find you a woman.

02:13.700 --> 02:17.329
Come on. We're going to
the darkest bar in town.

02:17.437 --> 02:20.463
<i>##[Disco]</i>

02:22.909 --> 02:24.843
<i>##[Continues]</i>

02:27.780 --> 02:30.271
Uh, I don't know, Homer.
Women can smell panic...

02:30.383 --> 02:32.681
and, uh, right now,
I gotta be reeking of it.

02:32.785 --> 02:35.948
Relax. All I smell is
garlic and fish.

02:36.055 --> 02:38.023
[Sighs]

02:40.126 --> 02:42.185
Uh, you look pretty clean.

02:42.295 --> 02:44.388
You, uh, mind
if I have this dance?

02:44.497 --> 02:46.522
- It's all yours.
- [Sighs]

02:48.001 --> 02:51.061
Okay, I won't lie to you.
A lot of people saw that.

02:51.171 --> 02:53.969
But you gotta
keep trying.

02:54.073 --> 02:56.439
[Clears Throat]
So, hi there.

02:56.543 --> 02:59.103
- Uh, don't scream.
- Oh, hi.

02:59.212 --> 03:01.271
Want to join me
for a Bacardi and soda?

03:01.381 --> 03:03.849
Yeah! Yeah,
that'd be great.

03:03.950 --> 03:07.511
Or maybe you'd prefer
a cool, refreshing Bacardi colada.

03:07.620 --> 03:10.316
- Sure. Whatever.
- Because Bacardi makes the night...

03:10.423 --> 03:12.323
come alive
with freshness.

03:12.425 --> 03:14.393
Uh, do you work
for Bacardi?

03:14.494 --> 03:16.485
No. I'm in love with you.

03:17.330 --> 03:19.457
[Whimpers]

03:19.566 --> 03:21.932
Hey, don't give up, Moe.

03:22.035 --> 03:24.765
The girl of your dreams
has gotta be in <i>some</i> bar.

03:25.972 --> 03:27.997
Aw, there's nobody for Moe.

03:28.107 --> 03:32.009
I'm just gonna die
lonely and ugly and... dead.

03:32.111 --> 03:34.909
- <i>[Woman] Well, hello, Mary Sunshine.</i>
- Huh?

03:35.014 --> 03:37.949
Aw, cheer up.
Here, have a flower.

03:38.051 --> 03:39.951
All right, come on.
What's the catch?

03:40.053 --> 03:43.022
A gorgeous woman don't just
hand you a free "daffy-dil."

03:43.122 --> 03:45.022
Really? You think
I'm gorgeous?

03:45.124 --> 03:47.217
Yeah, well,
the part that's showing.

03:47.327 --> 03:51.388
I guess you could have a lot of weird scars
or a fake ass or something.

03:51.497 --> 03:53.727
You don't talk
to a lot of women, do you?

03:53.833 --> 03:57.200
Well, no-no-
Well, no, not a lot. I've-

03:57.303 --> 04:00.170
Gee, I'm sorry. I used to box,
you know. My brairs-

04:00.273 --> 04:02.207
Well, it's kind of
in and out.

04:02.308 --> 04:05.038
Oh, that's awful.
And look at your little ears.

04:05.144 --> 04:07.635
Yeah, there's
extensive cauliflowering.

04:07.747 --> 04:09.977
Well, your bow tie
is just darling.

04:10.083 --> 04:12.916
[Laughing]
Oh, well, thanks.

04:13.019 --> 04:16.250
Yeah, it kind of draws the eye
away from the old mug.

04:16.356 --> 04:18.290
I like a face
with character.

04:18.391 --> 04:20.858
Let's get out of here, Moe.
This is going nowhere.

04:20.959 --> 04:25.727
Yeah, l- Look, I don't suppose
you'd ever want to, uh-

04:25.832 --> 04:28.699
I don't know-
get together sometime?

04:28.801 --> 04:32.669
You mean, like a date?
Well, I don't know.

04:32.772 --> 04:36.902
Oh, what was I thinking? A beautiful girl
like you and a gargoyle like me.

04:37.010 --> 04:38.944
- l-I'm sorry.
- Hold on. Hold on.

04:39.045 --> 04:41.275
- I didn't say "no" exactly.
- Really?

04:41.381 --> 04:44.350
Hot damn! All right, don't eat nothir
for the next three days...

04:44.450 --> 04:47.578
'cause I'm taking you out
for a steak the size of a toilet seat.

04:47.687 --> 04:50.212
Well, when you
put it that way-

04:50.323 --> 04:54.384
- My name is Renee.
- Who cares? You're goir out with me.

04:54.494 --> 04:56.394
She's going
out with me, cat!

04:57.830 --> 05:00.128
<i>[Homer]</i>
<i>Stop kissir that cat, and get in the car!</i>

05:00.300 --> 05:02.131
<i>##[Man Singing]</i>

05:12.512 --> 05:14.742
<i>##[Continues]</i>

05:29.329 --> 05:31.263
<i>##[Ends]</i>

05:33.666 --> 05:35.463
Hey, hey! Sabu!

05:35.568 --> 05:38.537
Uh, I need another magnum of
your best champagne here, huh?

05:38.638 --> 05:41.937
And bring us the finest food you got
stuffed with the second finest.

05:42.041 --> 05:46.273
Excellent, sir.
Lobster stuffed with tacos.

05:46.379 --> 05:49.746
<i>[Renee, Moe Laughing]</i>

05:49.849 --> 05:54.218
So, Renee, it looks like
you've taken quite a shine to Moe.

05:54.320 --> 05:56.220
Do you mind if I ask why?

05:56.322 --> 05:59.814
- Marge-
- I didn't mean any disrespect.

05:59.926 --> 06:02.019
I just can't
figure it out.

06:02.128 --> 06:04.961
Well, to be honest,
at first it was just pity.

06:05.064 --> 06:08.625
- Ah.
- Yeah, it's like out of a storybook, ain't it?

06:08.735 --> 06:10.965
But he's really
grown on me.

06:11.070 --> 06:15.769
- He's got this insecure, sweaty charm.
- Oh, yeah, I got that.

06:15.875 --> 06:19.868
And he's so thoughtful. Last night
he bought all the seats in a movie theater...

06:19.979 --> 06:23.380
- just so we could have
a romantic evening together.
- Yeah, well...

06:23.483 --> 06:27.419
I just get so tired of idiots shooting
their mouths off, laughing and clapping.

06:27.520 --> 06:29.420
Makes you wanna start
poking eyes out...

06:29.522 --> 06:31.615
- and slashing guts and kicking throats.
- It's okay, Moe.

06:31.724 --> 06:34.454
I'm sorry. It's just
I'm so happy I met you.

06:34.560 --> 06:37.256
<i>Uh, excuse me, sir.</i>
<i>Will there be anything else?</i>

06:37.363 --> 06:41.322
Uh, yeah. Park the dessert can't under
this beautiful lady's nose...

06:41.434 --> 06:43.766
and charge it all
to my Players Club card.

06:43.870 --> 06:47.431
Ooh, Players Club!
Yes, sir!

06:47.540 --> 06:50.270
<i>Yeah, I want to send her</i>
<i>two dozen roses.</i>

06:50.376 --> 06:53.777
And I want to put something nice
on the card, like, um-

06:53.880 --> 06:56.747
- Uh, "Renee, my treasure-"
- <i>[Laughing]</i>

06:58.151 --> 07:00.676
Hey, shut up, or I'll ram
a stool down your throat!

07:00.787 --> 07:03.347
Uh, no. No, no. I don't
want that on the card.

07:03.456 --> 07:05.356
Well, let me hear
how it sounds.

07:06.726 --> 07:08.626
Nah, nah, take it out.
Take it out.

07:08.728 --> 07:11.356
And charge it
to my Players Club card.

07:11.464 --> 07:13.364
Maxed out?
[Sighs]

07:13.466 --> 07:15.366
Look, I really need
these flowers, okay?

07:15.468 --> 07:18.995
I got a real tenuous hold
on my girlfriend here.

07:19.105 --> 07:21.335
- [Dial Tone]
- Hello? Hello?

07:24.010 --> 07:25.944
Well, that's it.
It's all over.

07:26.045 --> 07:29.071
Renee ain't gonna want to hang around
with noJoe Pinchpenny.

07:29.182 --> 07:33.084
Aw, come on, Moe. Think of all
you have to offer besides money.

07:34.987 --> 07:36.887
I need cash and lots of it.

07:36.989 --> 07:39.856
Um, all right, everybody,
I'm calling in your bar tabs.

07:39.959 --> 07:42.325
[Clamoring]

07:42.428 --> 07:44.828
You bunch
of ungrateful ingrates!

07:44.931 --> 07:47.422
You-Aw, Homer,
what am I gonna do?

07:47.533 --> 07:50.093
Renee's my last chance
for true love.

07:50.203 --> 07:54.230
If you really need money, you could sell
a kidney or maybe even your car.

07:55.341 --> 07:58.777
Nah, my car
ain't won'th nothir.

07:58.878 --> 08:01.870
But it is insured
for five grand.

08:01.981 --> 08:05.508
Homer, I need your help. You gotta
steal this car and wreck it for me.

08:05.618 --> 08:08.519
Steal? Oh, no,
you got the wrong guy.

08:09.622 --> 08:11.920
- You dropped somethir.
- Come on, Homer.

08:12.024 --> 08:14.151
I'm one of your dearest friends.
When everybody said...

08:14.260 --> 08:17.423
you were too drunk to drive that time,
who gave you your keys?

08:17.530 --> 08:19.725
Oh.
You did.

08:19.832 --> 08:22.392
But... I still don't know.

08:22.502 --> 08:24.970
I can just imagine
what Marge would say.

08:25.071 --> 08:27.369
Homer, I insist
you steal that car.

08:27.473 --> 08:29.373
I'll do it!

08:33.111 --> 08:37.344
Okay, here's the plan.
This model car represents my car, huh?

08:37.450 --> 08:39.941
And this olive
is you. Now-

08:40.052 --> 08:43.145
- Mmm! Me.
- Hey, hey! Aw, that's great.

08:43.256 --> 08:45.747
Now the car's gonna
have to represent you, and, uh...

08:45.858 --> 08:48.850
this little toy man
will represent the car.

08:48.961 --> 08:51.088
All right, forget it.
Forget it. Listen up here.

08:51.197 --> 08:55.463
Tomorrow night at 8:00, you go down
to the waterfront, and you steal my car.

08:55.568 --> 08:57.559
- What about the cops?
- That's the beauty part.

08:57.670 --> 09:01.436
Every cop in towrs gonna be on the police
department's Moonlight Charity Cruise...

09:01.541 --> 09:03.532
and I'm gonna be
right there with 'em.

09:03.643 --> 09:06.271
So, as soon
as you get back...

09:06.379 --> 09:08.279
we steal the car, right?

09:08.381 --> 09:12.715
Ri- No, no, wrong. Listen.
While I'm on the boat with the perfect alibi...

09:12.818 --> 09:15.981
you steal my car and park it
on the railroad tracks.

09:16.088 --> 09:19.819
Then when the 10:15 train
comes along-wham!

09:19.926 --> 09:21.985
Insurance company
pays off 5,000 clams.

09:22.094 --> 09:23.994
I keep showing Renee
the sweet life.

09:24.096 --> 09:26.564
You're a genius, Moe.
All your troubles...

09:26.666 --> 09:29.032
will soon be over
for a couple of months.

09:35.675 --> 09:37.802
- Why all the black?
- Why all the pearls?

09:37.910 --> 09:39.707
Why all the hair?
Why anything?

09:39.812 --> 09:41.746
You look a little
nervous, Dad.

09:41.847 --> 09:44.213
No, <i>you</i> look
a little nervous, Lisa.

09:44.317 --> 09:46.547
- You're up to something aren't you?
- No!

09:46.652 --> 09:49.849
I'm just going out
to commit certain deeds.

09:49.956 --> 09:51.856
[Under Breath]
Suckers.

09:56.062 --> 09:58.257
Thank you.
Welcome, folks. Have fun.

09:58.364 --> 10:00.764
Drink responsibly...
till we're a mile out.

10:00.866 --> 10:05.030
- [Chuckles]
- Uh, scuse me there, Officer.
You see my car there...

10:05.137 --> 10:08.629
with the rubber
hippie daisy, space 7 A?

10:08.741 --> 10:11.232
- Uh, yeah. What about it?
- I was just thinking...

10:11.344 --> 10:13.676
what a good parking job
I did with it.

10:13.779 --> 10:18.443
Yeah, hey, that is nice. Hey, Lou!
Lou, check out that park job in 7 A.

10:18.551 --> 10:20.485
Whoo-hoo-hoo.
That's sweet.

10:24.890 --> 10:26.790
[Giggles]

10:26.892 --> 10:29.326
I'm going to be
the best car thief ever.

10:29.428 --> 10:32.363
Hey! Oh, no, you don't!

10:32.465 --> 10:34.365
- [Grunts]
- [Groans] Ow.

10:35.701 --> 10:39.228
[Laughs]
He thought he was gonna steal-

10:39.338 --> 10:41.306
D'oh!

10:41.407 --> 10:44.968
<i>##[Homer Singing]</i>

10:49.782 --> 10:51.875
They're showing
<i>Hail to the Chimp!</i>

10:51.984 --> 10:53.975
I have time to see
one little movie.

10:56.756 --> 10:59.350
[Man] Mr. President,
your welfare proposal...

10:59.458 --> 11:02.723
is nothing but a lot of technical jargon
and partisan rhetoric and-

11:02.828 --> 11:04.728
- [Shrieking]
- [Screaming]

11:04.830 --> 11:06.730
Get off me,
Mr. President!

11:06.832 --> 11:10.529
[Laughs] That's what you get
for not hailing to the chimp.

11:18.344 --> 11:21.643
Moe, you seem awfully
distracted tonight.

11:21.747 --> 11:24.648
- And you're sweating a lot, even for you.
- Am I?

11:24.750 --> 11:26.650
Huh. Hadrt noticed.

11:26.752 --> 11:28.617
Whoo-ah!

11:28.721 --> 11:31.053
<i>[Renee]</i>
<i>Isn't it a beautiful moon tonight?</i>

11:31.157 --> 11:33.250
Huh? Oh, yeah.
Yeah, yeah.

11:33.359 --> 11:35.919
- I'll look up with you in one minute.
- <i>[Train Whistle Blows]</i>

11:36.028 --> 11:38.155
The train. You hear that?
That's the train!

11:38.264 --> 11:40.926
Isn't that the most beautiful sound
you ever heard?

11:41.033 --> 11:43.433
It's almost as sweet
as your voice.

11:43.536 --> 11:45.436
Aw!

11:51.343 --> 11:53.903
- <i>[Train Approaching]</i>
- Huh?

11:55.047 --> 11:56.981
Oh, no.
The train!

12:05.925 --> 12:09.053
D'oh! I gotta find
another way to wreck Moe's car.

12:11.397 --> 12:14.833
Oh, honey, this whole evening
was so wonderful.

12:14.934 --> 12:18.233
Except when that drunken cop
started firing at those seagulls.

12:18.337 --> 12:20.737
- <i>[Seagull Cawing]</i>
- Ah! Get 'em off!

12:20.840 --> 12:23.104
Yeah. Yeah, the plan
went off without a hitch.

12:23.209 --> 12:26.667
- What plan?
- The what? The-The wonderful evening plan.

12:26.779 --> 12:29.009
<i>Hey, Moe. Isn't that</i>
<i>your car up there...</i>

12:29.115 --> 12:31.015
with the rubber
hippie daisy...

12:31.117 --> 12:32.914
<i>the one that</i>
<i>was parked in 7 A?</i>

12:33.018 --> 12:35.987
Hey! Hey, what's
it doing there?

12:36.088 --> 12:38.147
It was supposed to be
on the railroad tracks.

12:38.257 --> 12:40.555
No, I mean,
the parking lot.

12:41.994 --> 12:45.225
- Homer, you moron.
- Homer, you genius!

12:45.331 --> 12:47.231
[Chuckles]

12:47.333 --> 12:49.528
Geronimo!
[Grunting]

12:51.470 --> 12:52.903
Huh?

12:53.005 --> 12:55.530
[Screaming]

12:57.476 --> 12:59.637
[Whimpering]

13:01.080 --> 13:03.048
[Gasps, Sighs]

13:03.149 --> 13:06.277
[Screaming]

13:09.255 --> 13:11.052
[Sighs]

13:11.157 --> 13:14.058
[Screaming]

13:16.996 --> 13:19.226
<i>[Screams]</i>

13:23.068 --> 13:26.595
Huh. Well, that car thief
can't hold his breath forever.

13:26.705 --> 13:29.970
- And if he can, Chief?
- Then God help us all.

13:33.012 --> 13:35.037
<i>[Guns Cocking]</i>

13:35.147 --> 13:39.015
- Isn't that your friend Homer?
- Uh, oh, oh!

13:39.118 --> 13:42.986
Homer!
Oh, how... could you?

13:43.088 --> 13:45.750
You're under arrest, Simpson,
for grand theft auto.

13:45.858 --> 13:48.554
- Now put up your hands.
- [Whimpers]

13:50.863 --> 13:53.127
Brilliant! Brilliant!
Okay, let's do another...

13:53.232 --> 13:55.598
but this time,
try to look scarier.

13:55.701 --> 13:57.601
Kind of like-
[Growls]

13:57.703 --> 14:01.002
- Grr.
- Gorgeous! Gorgeous, baby. That's it. That's it.

14:03.008 --> 14:05.476
Your fingerprints are
just like snowflakes.

14:05.578 --> 14:07.478
They're both very pretty.

14:07.580 --> 14:10.140
<i>[Lou]</i>
<i>Simpson! You have visitors.</i>

14:11.917 --> 14:14.511
Homer, did you
really steal a car?

14:14.620 --> 14:17.589
Whoa! Hang on a minute.
The guard said I had visitors coming.

14:17.690 --> 14:19.658
Dad, we're the visitors.

14:19.758 --> 14:22.625
Oh. Oh. Oh!
Oh, great.

14:22.728 --> 14:25.856
Listen, I know it looks bad,
but all I can tell you...

14:25.965 --> 14:29.196
is I destroyed that car
for all the right reasons.

14:29.301 --> 14:31.769
I'd like to
believe you-

14:31.871 --> 14:34.567
That's my girl.
You just go home...

14:34.673 --> 14:37.141
and don't worry your pretty
blue head about it.

14:37.243 --> 14:39.575
Moe will take care
of everything.

14:39.678 --> 14:42.909
Well, in the meantime, here's a can'ton
of smokes you can use to buy stuff.

14:43.015 --> 14:44.949
Aw, thanks, boy.

14:45.050 --> 14:47.883
- I'll give you two packs for that candy bar.
- Three.

14:47.987 --> 14:50.751
- Why, you little-
- Guard! Guard!

14:50.856 --> 14:53.051
<i>[Snoring]</i>

14:53.158 --> 14:56.321
<i>[Moe]</i>
<i>Rsst! Homer. Homer, wake up.</i>

14:56.428 --> 14:58.896
Moe! Oh, Moe,
thank God you're here!

14:58.998 --> 15:02.695
Yeah, congratulations, Homer.
The plan worked perfectly.

15:02.801 --> 15:05.599
- But I'm in jail.
- Yeah. Yeah, that's a-

15:05.704 --> 15:09.731
- That's a kick in the pants.
- Moe, you gotta get me out of here.

15:09.842 --> 15:13.175
Tell the cops I didn't steal the car.
Say you lent it to me.

15:13.279 --> 15:15.679
Yeah, I wish I could, Homer.
But if I change my story...

15:15.781 --> 15:17.681
they're gonna
throw me in here.

15:17.783 --> 15:21.184
But, Moe, we're best friends.

15:22.588 --> 15:25.819
Oh, cripes,
the puppy dog look.

15:25.925 --> 15:27.950
[Sighs]
All right, all right.

15:28.060 --> 15:30.460
I'll use the money
to bail you out.

15:30.562 --> 15:34.999
Hurry, Moe. At 3:00, they're gonna
put us in the exercise yard.

15:35.100 --> 15:37.568
The exercise yard!

15:37.670 --> 15:40.764
Is everything okay, honey?
Your shirt is so dry.

15:40.873 --> 15:44.036
